1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:07,600
Let's get a divorce.

2
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:09,280
I won't let it end so easily.

3
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:11,640
I've already talked to Pun
about everything.

4
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:13,120
It's over now.

5
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:15,800
But I won't let it end!

6
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:20,040
Please don't let what happened with Win
destroy everything.

7
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:22,200
Just say whether you love me or not.

8
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:25,400
What's so hard about that?

9
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:29,320
- Huh?!
- Pun!

10
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:31,880
- You really want to die, huh?
- Pun!

11
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,920
Pun! Stop!

12
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:34,880
Let go!

13
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:47,680
Pie!

14
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:20,440
Auntie, please sit down.

15
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:40,400
WIN

16
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:08,240
What's up, Win?

17
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:11,560
Rok, how's Pie doing right now?

18
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:13,880
How did you know I'm at the hospital?

19
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:15,600
And where are you?

20
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:17,839
I'm nearby.

21
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:21,279
So, how's Pie? Is she okay?

22
00:04:21,959 --> 00:04:24,560
She has a brain hemorrhage
and an ankle ligament injury.

23
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:28,680
<i>The surgery is done,</i>
<i>but she hasn't woken up yet.</i>

24
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:32,560
The doctor had to move her
to the ICU for observation.

25
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:39,320
She'll be okay, right?

26
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:42,720
The doctor hasn't confirmed yet.

27
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:45,080
They need to monitor her after surgery.

28
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:47,040
She's still in critical condition.

29
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,920
Okay, thanks a lot, Rok.

30
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:18,440
Mom, you should go home and rest.

31
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:19,840
I'll stay with Pie.

32
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:24,120
No, I'm worried about her.
I want to be here too.

33
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:28,160
I said go home, so please do.

34
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,640
I can take care of her.

35
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:12,320
<i>She's going to Pun because of your debts.</i>

36
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:15,600
<i>She has done everything for you</i>
<i>her whole life.</i>

37
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:19,160
<i>When was the last time you saw her happy?</i>

38
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,680
<i>If you really cared,</i>

39
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:26,480
<i>you'd know that she hasn't been happy</i>
<i>for a long time.</i>

40
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:30,000
Auntie.

41
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,600
Are you okay?

42
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:41,280
You're right.

43
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:45,040
Pie hasn't been happy for a long time.

44
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:50,480
She's suffered because of me.

45
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:53,840
I made her like this.

46
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:00,480
Pie is the only one I have.

47
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:03,120
I treated her like she was my possession.

48
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:07,400
And sometimes,
I forgot she has her own life.

49
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,720
If I hadn't caused all this,

50
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:13,040
she wouldn't have to fix my mistakes,

51
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:16,600
she wouldn't have to go through this pain.

52
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:23,520
It's all because of me.

53
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:28,240
I've taken advantage of her love too much.

54
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,720
Rok.

55
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:39,840
Pie will be safe, right?

56
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:43,480
She'll wake up, right, Rok?

57
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:49,240
<i>It's my fault. It's all on me, Pun.</i>

58
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:53,200
<i>If you're angry or disappointed,</i>
<i>it's because of me, not anyone else.</i>

59
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:54,840
I love Pie!

60
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:57,320
There's never been a day
I haven't thought about her.

61
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,000
<i>I want to protect her.</i>

62
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:01,880
<i>I don't want her to be hurt again.</i>

63
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:39,920
Where's Nhun?

64
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:43,200
She went out a while ago
with Miss Mungmink.

65
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:45,800
Then let her know I'm going to the temple.

66
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,200
Yes, sir.

67
00:10:58,480 --> 00:11:00,920
Will this really work, Mink?

68
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,400
The coordinates are spot on.

69
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:05,000
We'll find him for sure. Don't worry.

70
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:11,000
<i>Oh? Where are you going?</i>

71
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:12,200
I'm going on my meditation retreat.

72
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:14,840
- Are you going to practice meditation?
- Yes.

73
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:17,520
There's the summer novice ordination
the day after tomorrow.

74
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:19,960
<i>I'll help out at the temple</i>
<i>for a couple of days.</i>

75
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:43,640
This isn't a temple, Auntie.

76
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:49,200
What are you going to do now?

77
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:54,800
Auntie.

78
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:57,200
Are you okay?

79
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:09,240
Are you hungry?
I made some <i>Gaeng Som</i> for you.

80
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:11,120
- Oh, perfect!
- Want to eat now?

81
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,760
- I'll throw the box away first.
- Okay.

82
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:14,240
- Go ahead, serve it.
- Okay.

83
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:15,920
Oh, do you want to hold it, dear?

84
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,880
Wanna hold it?

85
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:28,600
Nhun.

86
00:12:35,160 --> 00:12:36,320
Please calm down.

87
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:37,640
Listen to me first.

88
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:50,120
Get out.

89
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:53,080
I want to talk to my husband privately.

90
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:02,800
It's okay, dear.

91
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,720
How long has it been?

92
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:16,720
I'm asking how long have you been lying,
pretending to go meditate?

93
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:19,000
Since last year.

94
00:13:20,880 --> 00:13:22,280
From the beginning, right?

95
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:27,240
You never really went
to meditate, did you?

96
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:29,120
I'm sorry.

97
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,320
Why?

98
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:34,160
Why?! What did I do wrong?

99
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:43,720
No one's at fault.

100
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:47,320
We just don't love each other anymore.

101
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,840
Our love is gone.

102
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,760
Don't say our love is gone.

103
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:56,120
Because mine isn't.
And don't say no one's to blame.

104
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:59,480
You're the one at fault. Totally!

105
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:01,520
Okay.

106
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:03,480
I'm the one at fault.

107
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:07,600
I was wrong to start seeing her
before telling you the truth.

108
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:08,800
Yes!

109
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:13,160
And when you said our love was gone,

110
00:14:13,680 --> 00:14:17,840
tell me, when exactly did it end? Huh?

111
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:21,800
Nhun.

112
00:14:23,160 --> 00:14:25,960
We've never been happy together.

113
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:29,400
Everything I do seems to annoy you.

114
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:31,360
Nothing I say ever sounds right.

115
00:14:32,520 --> 00:14:33,520
You even said

116
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:36,240
that when I'm not at home,
you feel better.

117
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:37,640
You sleep easier.

118
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:41,920
That's what they call love being gone.

119
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:45,200
I'm annoyed with you
because you've changed.

120
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:48,520
You weren't this stubborn
and difficult before.

121
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:52,840
I wasn't being myself
because I was forcing it.

122
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:57,120
I did everything you wanted.

123
00:14:57,200 --> 00:15:00,040
But I can't keep doing it.

124
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:03,400
I want to be myself,

125
00:15:03,480 --> 00:15:05,200
and you can't accept that.

126
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:07,680
Then why did you put up with it before?

127
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:10,560
Why didn't you ever tell me
how you really felt?

128
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:13,680
Why didn't you say anything?
Why didn't you tell me?!

129
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:14,800
Nhun!

130
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:22,000
I've tried talking, but you never listen.

131
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:24,800
The more I talk, the more you get annoyed.

132
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:28,040
At this point,
what's the point of speaking?

133
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:29,960
It's useless!

134
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:32,360
Listen.

135
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:36,280
Our love can't go on anymore.

136
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,440
Let's get a divorce.

137
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:48,520
You want a divorce from me?

138
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:53,560
This way, we can go our separate ways
and live the rest of our lives happily,

139
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:55,680
the way we want.

140
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:58,640
We're not young anymore.

141
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:01,480
Let's not force this, Nhun.

142
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:04,280
No! I won't divorce you!

143
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:05,440
Nhun.

144
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:08,680
Our marriage can't go on.

145
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:11,480
Accept it.

146
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:13,960
No, I won't accept it!

147
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:17,240
I won't give up. I won't divorce you!

148
00:16:23,160 --> 00:16:24,080
Nhun.

149
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,320
Nhun!

150
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:27,480
- Nhun!
- Let me go.

151
00:16:27,560 --> 00:16:29,360
Can we talk this through first?

152
00:16:29,960 --> 00:16:31,360
Let's end this properly.

153
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:35,520
After all this,
you still want a proper ending?

154
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:36,640
No way!

155
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:39,680
No matter what, I won't divorce.

156
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:42,040
Did you hear me? I won't divorce!

157
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:46,560
You'll be my husband's other woman
for the rest of your life,

158
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:49,200
carrying the title of a mistress forever.

159
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:50,400
Live with it!

160
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:54,680
That's enough, Nhun!

161
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:56,360
Kwan doesn't know anything.

162
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:58,080
If you want to blame, blame me!

163
00:16:58,160 --> 00:16:59,040
I don't believe she doesn't know.

164
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:01,640
That's enough, Auntie.

165
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:03,280
Let's go home, please.

166
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:05,040
No, I'm going to yell at them!

167
00:17:05,119 --> 00:17:07,160
You two have no shame!

168
00:17:07,839 --> 00:17:09,760
- How could you do this behind my back?
- Auntie!

169
00:17:09,839 --> 00:17:11,520
- Let's go home!
- Shameless woman!

170
00:17:11,599 --> 00:17:13,480
- That's enough.
- You greedy man!

171
00:17:13,560 --> 00:17:15,480
- Auntie!
- You bastard!

172
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:26,920
It's okay, dear.

173
00:17:27,599 --> 00:17:29,720
Auntie.

174
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:38,360
Auntie!

175
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:39,280
<i>Why not try keeping the five precepts?</i>

176
00:18:39,360 --> 00:18:40,760
Especially the third one.

177
00:18:41,360 --> 00:18:43,640
<i>Maybe then you'll stop meddling</i>
<i>in others' families.</i>

178
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:30,120
Nurse, my wife's awake!

179
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:39,640
Doctor, the patient
in ICU room 2 is awake.

180
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,600
Yes, Doctor.

181
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:42,520
‪Alright.

182
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:46,760
KDMS ORTHOPEDIC HOSPITAL

183
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:04,480
This is…

184
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:08,080
a hospital?

185
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:12,400
Yes, you've been here since yesterday.

186
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:21,240
How did I get here?

187
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:23,000
Your family brought you.

188
00:20:23,840 --> 00:20:27,120
Now, please listen carefully
to my questions.

189
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:29,880
Think slowly and answer
each one carefully.

190
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:32,040
Okay.

191
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:40,360
I'm going to do a quick check, alright?

192
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:41,560
Okay.

193
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:44,200
Look at my face, not the light.

194
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,600
Alright.

195
00:20:48,640 --> 00:20:49,640
Good.

196
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:54,240
Look at my finger now.
Don't turn your head.

197
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:55,520
Just follow with your eyes.

198
00:20:56,120 --> 00:20:57,120
Good.

199
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:01,560
Good.

200
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:05,880
What's your name?

201
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:11,040
Phitpicha Attwijit.

202
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:13,120
Do you know this person?

203
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:17,480
Yes, I do.

204
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:20,560
Do you remember his name?

205
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:24,680
Pun.

206
00:21:25,240 --> 00:21:27,240
What is your relationship with him?

207
00:21:30,240 --> 00:21:31,600
He's my husband.

208
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:35,720
Can you recall what happened before?

209
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:38,880
Can you tell me what happened
before you got to the hospital?

210
00:21:46,280 --> 00:21:47,520
I…

211
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:53,080
I drove to an old house to see him.

212
00:21:58,560 --> 00:22:01,160
We talked on the second floor,

213
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:03,600
and…

214
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:16,760
I can't remember.

215
00:22:17,560 --> 00:22:20,520
I'm not sure what happened
after that, Doctor.

216
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:25,120
It hurts.

217
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:30,760
My leg! It hurts.

218
00:22:31,360 --> 00:22:35,240
May I have you try lifting your left leg?

219
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:37,440
Okay.

220
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:45,120
Can you try your left arm as well?

221
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:54,680
Doctor, I can't lift it at all.

222
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:56,520
Doctor.

223
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:58,960
What happened?

224
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:03,600
Well, the patient's left arm
is likely weak

225
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:06,080
due to a bruise
on the right side of the brain.

226
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:09,280
I'll have her consult
with the physiotherapist.

227
00:23:09,880 --> 00:23:12,560
With daily therapy,
her condition should improve.

228
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:15,120
We'll move her from the ICU

229
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:17,360
to a private room.

230
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:20,000
I'll check her again tomorrow.

231
00:23:31,880 --> 00:23:32,720
<i>Doctor.</i>

232
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:36,720
Why can't Pie remember what happened
before she came to the hospital?

233
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:41,920
The accident caused trauma
to parts of the brain,

234
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:44,520
affecting short-term memory.

235
00:23:44,600 --> 00:23:47,200
She won't remember what just happened,

236
00:23:47,280 --> 00:23:50,440
but her memory should gradually return.

237
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:04,000
And what about her ankle and the weakness
in her arm and leg?

238
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:06,360
Her ankle ligament is inflamed.

239
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:08,160
If there are no complications,

240
00:24:08,240 --> 00:24:11,840
with medication and care,
it should heal soon.

241
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:14,040
As for the weakness in her arm and leg,

242
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:16,960
the physiotherapy team
will take care of it.

243
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:22,560
Please excuse me.

244
00:24:23,160 --> 00:24:24,400
Thank you.

245
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:42,800
Pun, Pie's awake?

246
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:45,320
How's her condition?

247
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:15,400
<i>Pie's awake and out of danger.</i>

248
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:26,800
I'm sorry, dear.

249
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:31,400
I've been selfish.

250
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:35,000
I've taken advantage of you in every way.

251
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:40,880
I've been a terrible mother.

252
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:51,920
Mom…

253
00:25:54,280 --> 00:25:56,080
I'm okay.

254
00:25:58,360 --> 00:26:02,880
Stay strong and get well soon.

255
00:26:05,320 --> 00:26:07,760
Stay with me a long time, okay?

256
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:12,200
Please don't get hurt again.

257
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:18,320
Don't cry, Mom.

258
00:26:24,840 --> 00:26:26,240
I promise,

259
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:29,960
I'll change myself.

260
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:35,320
I won't put my problems on you anymore.

261
00:26:38,160 --> 00:26:40,880
I'll handle everything myself.

262
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:45,480
I won't make you sad again, Pie.

263
00:26:45,560 --> 00:26:47,200
Okay?

264
00:26:58,680 --> 00:27:00,520
Pie's lost her memory?

265
00:27:02,560 --> 00:27:04,200
It's only short-term memory.

266
00:27:04,960 --> 00:27:07,800
She won't remember
what happened during the accident.

267
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:12,560
So what exactly happened, Pun?

268
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:15,160
Why is she in such bad shape?

269
00:27:23,520 --> 00:27:24,720
It's my fault.

270
00:27:27,240 --> 00:27:29,000
I caused this to Pie.

271
00:27:33,440 --> 00:27:34,480
Pun.

272
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:40,200
You told me yourself it was an accident.

273
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:42,760
You didn't mean it.

274
00:27:44,320 --> 00:27:46,120
Don't blame yourself.

275
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:13,480
I'll go talk to Pie first.

276
00:28:39,040 --> 00:28:39,960
Pun.

277
00:28:43,920 --> 00:28:45,680
I've put the house up for sale.

278
00:28:47,760 --> 00:28:49,560
Once it's sold,

279
00:28:50,760 --> 00:28:52,640
I'll pay you back immediately.

280
00:28:55,560 --> 00:28:57,000
Don't worry about the debt.

281
00:28:57,880 --> 00:28:59,120
I'm not rushing it anymore.

282
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:02,080
I'll have the lawyer put a hold on it.

283
00:29:03,280 --> 00:29:06,880
No, I don't want to make Pie
feel uncomfortable.

284
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:10,080
Once it's sold, I'll pay off all the debt.

285
00:29:10,600 --> 00:29:12,880
I don't want to cause her
any more problems.

286
00:29:18,120 --> 00:29:19,600
If that's what you want,

287
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:23,960
then do as you wish.

288
00:29:25,800 --> 00:29:27,680
As for her treatment,

289
00:29:29,320 --> 00:29:31,040
I'll take full responsibility.

290
00:29:32,520 --> 00:29:34,560
I'll take care of her
until she's fully recovered.

291
00:29:39,160 --> 00:29:40,320
Okay.

292
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:43,320
Once the debt is cleared,

293
00:29:43,400 --> 00:29:45,880
there should be some money left.

294
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:48,000
I'll help out too.

295
00:29:48,840 --> 00:29:49,960
It's okay.

296
00:29:52,080 --> 00:29:53,640
I'll take care of Pie.

297
00:29:56,400 --> 00:29:59,080
I'll look after her
until she's completely well.

298
00:30:10,120 --> 00:30:13,360
Rok, I don't have any hair left.
What am I gonna do?

299
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:15,400
It'll grow back. Look at my hair.

300
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:17,280
It'll grow back.

301
00:30:17,360 --> 00:30:19,960
Don't worry. No, no!

302
00:30:20,040 --> 00:30:21,000
- Okay.
- Okay?

303
00:30:21,080 --> 00:30:22,320
- Yeah.
- Hey, Pie.

304
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:23,880
Huh?

305
00:30:24,920 --> 00:30:26,520
I quit.

306
00:30:27,280 --> 00:30:29,080
I'm moving down south with Dad.

307
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:31,440
Mom's going too. The whole family's going.

308
00:30:33,480 --> 00:30:35,120
- Really?
- Yeah.

309
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:37,480
Alright.

310
00:30:41,040 --> 00:30:44,120
I just want you
to finally have a peaceful life.

311
00:30:46,160 --> 00:30:48,360
I've missed you so much.

312
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:52,760
Someone who can be happy with everything,

313
00:30:52,840 --> 00:30:53,960
I really missed you.

314
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:57,280
Hey, don't cry.

315
00:30:59,880 --> 00:31:01,560
I missed her too.

316
00:31:03,600 --> 00:31:04,720
Hey.

317
00:31:04,800 --> 00:31:08,600
The old Pie is still in you. Okay?

318
00:31:09,360 --> 00:31:11,240
Be happy again.

319
00:31:11,320 --> 00:31:16,080
I want you
to finally live the life you want, Pie.

320
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:19,560
If you get stuck or don't know what to do,

321
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:21,440
just call me.

322
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:24,920
I'll book a ticket
and fly to you right away. Okay?

323
00:31:27,440 --> 00:31:28,320
Promise?

324
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:29,560
Promise.

325
00:31:31,360 --> 00:31:34,000
Alright? Promise.

326
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:37,080
Stay strong!

327
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:39,800
Stay strong.

328
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:44,800
Good luck.

329
00:32:13,840 --> 00:32:14,720
Thanks.

330
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:22,960
I know what went on between Win and Pie.

331
00:32:26,280 --> 00:32:28,400
Do you know that when I found out,

332
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:32,440
I was so mad at those two
for lying and hiding the truth?

333
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:35,680
But looking at it their way…

334
00:32:37,760 --> 00:32:39,960
Maybe they just didn't want
to tell anyone.

335
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:43,800
They didn't mean
for things to turn out this way.

336
00:32:44,520 --> 00:32:47,280
Both Win and Pie deserve some sympathy.

337
00:32:49,840 --> 00:32:51,680
But the person I feel most for

338
00:32:52,440 --> 00:32:53,520
is you, Pun.

339
00:32:58,840 --> 00:33:03,280
You're probably angrier
and more disappointed than I am.

340
00:33:04,480 --> 00:33:08,560
I want to see my brother happy.

341
00:33:14,400 --> 00:33:16,800
Do you know you're such a nice person?

342
00:33:17,800 --> 00:33:20,160
Anyone around you loves you.

343
00:33:20,240 --> 00:33:24,120
But when you get angry,
you can be really, really scary.

344
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:26,920
If you keep losing your temper,
everyone around you

345
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:29,360
will end up running away.

346
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:33,600
I'm being honest because I love you

347
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:35,280
and I care about you.

348
00:33:50,680 --> 00:33:53,360
Thanks. Really, thanks a lot.

349
00:34:09,120 --> 00:34:10,560
I have to go now, Pun.

350
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:13,760
Oh.

351
00:34:14,400 --> 00:34:16,320
I don't know what's been happening,

352
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:20,440
but Aunt Nhun, Uncle Sil, and Mink
are looking for you.

353
00:34:21,520 --> 00:34:24,600
Make sure you get back to them.

354
00:34:25,120 --> 00:34:26,360
Got it.

355
00:34:33,199 --> 00:34:34,480
- Bye.
- Bye.

356
00:34:43,920 --> 00:34:45,719
PUN

357
00:34:51,440 --> 00:34:54,000
Pun, you told Mom, right?

358
00:34:58,320 --> 00:34:59,480
No, I didn't.

359
00:35:02,640 --> 00:35:04,040
But it's good that she knows now.

360
00:35:06,520 --> 00:35:07,840
How's she doing?

361
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:09,920
Not well.

362
00:35:10,680 --> 00:35:12,440
<i>She's hurt.</i>

363
00:35:13,800 --> 00:35:15,400
<i>I'm hurting too.</i>

364
00:35:15,920 --> 00:35:17,680
We've been together so long.

365
00:35:18,520 --> 00:35:19,760
Even if the love is gone,

366
00:35:20,440 --> 00:35:22,680
my bond with her isn't.

367
00:35:23,600 --> 00:35:26,280
I really didn't want to hurt her.

368
00:35:31,920 --> 00:35:33,920
I've been selfish.

369
00:35:34,600 --> 00:35:38,360
I'm sorry for what
I've done to our family.

370
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:40,200
I'm sorry.

371
00:35:41,720 --> 00:35:43,240
I'm really sorry.

372
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:48,320
You don't have to apologize, Dad.

373
00:35:51,280 --> 00:35:53,080
It happened.

374
00:35:56,600 --> 00:35:58,040
I forgive you.

375
00:36:04,040 --> 00:36:07,040
Thank you so much, Pun. Thank you.

376
00:36:32,400 --> 00:36:34,520
Pun, where have you been?

377
00:36:34,600 --> 00:36:37,480
Let's put that aside for now, Mink.
How's Mom?

378
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:41,280
She's asleep.

379
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:43,960
I gave her some calming tea,
and now she's resting.

380
00:36:45,840 --> 00:36:46,960
<i>You know what happened, right?</i>

381
00:36:48,360 --> 00:36:50,920
And where are you now?

382
00:36:53,280 --> 00:36:54,720
I'm at the hospital.

383
00:36:55,680 --> 00:36:57,040
There was an accident
at your great-grandmother's house.

384
00:36:57,120 --> 00:36:59,360
What? An accident?

385
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:01,480
Was anyone seriously hurt?

386
00:37:03,640 --> 00:37:04,920
Pie was injured.

387
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:07,920
But she's out of the ICU now.

388
00:37:09,040 --> 00:37:10,560
ICU?

389
00:37:10,640 --> 00:37:13,640
It must have been serious
that she ended up in the ICU.

390
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:18,360
How's Pie? Is she okay?

391
00:37:20,200 --> 00:37:21,320
It's serious.

392
00:37:22,440 --> 00:37:24,320
We'll talk about the details later, Mink.

393
00:37:25,320 --> 00:37:27,840
Please tell Mom I'll be home tomorrow.

394
00:37:28,600 --> 00:37:30,080
Take care of her for me.

395
00:37:31,120 --> 00:37:32,040
That's all for now.

396
00:37:33,320 --> 00:37:34,480
Yes, Pun.

397
00:37:47,280 --> 00:37:50,280
KRAROK

398
00:37:55,920 --> 00:37:56,800
Hello?

399
00:37:57,440 --> 00:37:58,680
How's Pie?

400
00:37:59,440 --> 00:38:02,280
She's tired and weak from the surgery.

401
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:03,640
Her arm and leg are weak,

402
00:38:03,720 --> 00:38:05,720
<i>and she has some pain at the incision.</i>

403
00:38:05,800 --> 00:38:08,320
<i>The doctor gave her painkillers</i>
<i>and told her to rest.</i>

404
00:38:09,680 --> 00:38:12,320
But she has short-term memory loss.

405
00:38:13,160 --> 00:38:14,640
She doesn't remember

406
00:38:14,720 --> 00:38:18,840
what happened to her
or why she's in the hospital.

407
00:38:25,400 --> 00:38:27,000
It's better that she doesn't remember.

408
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:31,600
You don't want Pie
to be mad at Pun, right?

409
00:38:32,240 --> 00:38:34,120
Pun did nothing wrong. It's my fault.

410
00:38:34,960 --> 00:38:37,240
If Pie asks, tell her it's because of me.

411
00:38:38,760 --> 00:38:42,560
You're both alike.
Pun and you are taking the blame.

412
00:38:42,640 --> 00:38:48,160
<i>Honestly, the tricky part is,</i>
<i>no one's really to blame.</i>

413
00:38:48,760 --> 00:38:52,400
I don't even know
if I should be angry or hate anyone.

414
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:55,200
<i>Everyone's at fault a little bit.</i>

415
00:38:56,320 --> 00:38:59,480
So just share the responsibility.
Don't carry it all alone.

416
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:06,320
Aren't you really going to visit Pie?

417
00:39:07,400 --> 00:39:09,040
Why are you hiding from her?

418
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:48,400
Pie, what's wrong?

419
00:39:50,520 --> 00:39:51,680
Pun…

420
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:55,280
I'm trying to remember

421
00:39:56,240 --> 00:39:57,880
what happened.

422
00:39:58,960 --> 00:40:00,320
But no matter how hard I try,

423
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:02,560
I just can't.

424
00:40:04,760 --> 00:40:06,120
I only recall

425
00:40:08,040 --> 00:40:10,560
talking with you about the debt

426
00:40:11,400 --> 00:40:12,920
and the divorce…

427
00:40:13,520 --> 00:40:14,400
And…

428
00:40:21,320 --> 00:40:22,760
Did we talk it through?

429
00:40:26,440 --> 00:40:27,480
Hey.

430
00:40:29,720 --> 00:40:33,080
Don't try to think about it, Pie.
Let it go for now.

431
00:40:35,800 --> 00:40:36,800
Pun.

432
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:40,800
What happened that day?

433
00:40:44,080 --> 00:40:46,200
Can you tell me?

434
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:52,400
I won't tell you anything yet.

435
00:40:53,600 --> 00:40:57,440
Focus on getting better first,
and then we'll talk.

436
00:40:59,040 --> 00:41:01,800
Right now, your health comes first.

437
00:41:01,880 --> 00:41:02,920
Trust me.

438
00:41:46,680 --> 00:41:49,480
Let me wipe you down a bit.
It'll help you recover faster.

439
00:42:45,640 --> 00:42:47,600
Surprise!

440
00:42:47,680 --> 00:42:49,400
- Oh, Dech?
- How's it going?

441
00:42:49,480 --> 00:42:51,080
Oh, careful.

442
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:52,720
You said you'd come back next month.

443
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:54,560
You've had it so bad.

444
00:42:54,640 --> 00:42:56,600
How could I just go out and enjoy myself?

445
00:42:58,000 --> 00:42:59,120
Are you okay?

446
00:43:00,640 --> 00:43:03,840
My husband cheated,
took a young woman as a mistress,

447
00:43:03,920 --> 00:43:05,240
and even had a baby.

448
00:43:05,320 --> 00:43:06,600
Who could handle that?

449
00:43:08,360 --> 00:43:10,880
Hey, you've been through so much.

450
00:43:10,960 --> 00:43:12,680
Can you go on?

451
00:43:12,760 --> 00:43:14,960
I say, get a divorce!

452
00:43:15,560 --> 00:43:17,280
You won't have to suffer anymore.

453
00:43:17,360 --> 00:43:21,000
No! Why would I divorce
and let those two be happy?

454
00:43:22,080 --> 00:43:25,000
And does this make you happy?

455
00:43:25,680 --> 00:43:27,680
I'm not happy either way.

456
00:43:27,760 --> 00:43:30,680
If I divorce, they're happy.

457
00:43:30,760 --> 00:43:34,320
If I don't, they're unhappy too.

458
00:43:34,400 --> 00:43:36,920
This way, everyone suffers equally.

459
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:39,320
Fair and square. Equal for all.

460
00:43:44,200 --> 00:43:45,400
<i>Who would've thought?</i>

461
00:43:45,480 --> 00:43:46,840
After all these years together,

462
00:43:46,920 --> 00:43:48,760
they have to separate
because of a third wheel.

463
00:43:51,160 --> 00:43:52,120
Hey, Mink.

464
00:43:52,200 --> 00:43:54,680
Don't ever come between Pun and Pie.

465
00:43:54,760 --> 00:43:56,120
It's not right.

466
00:43:56,200 --> 00:43:57,560
Look at Aunt Nhun, you see?

467
00:43:58,480 --> 00:44:01,280
Anyone caught in this kind of situation
can never be happy.

468
00:44:02,760 --> 00:44:05,200
I only just realized
from watching Aunt Nhun

469
00:44:05,280 --> 00:44:07,400
how painful it is
to have someone take away

470
00:44:07,920 --> 00:44:09,840
the person you love.

471
00:44:12,760 --> 00:44:15,560
I feel sorry that she has to suffer,

472
00:44:15,640 --> 00:44:17,640
even though she did nothing wrong.

473
00:44:22,000 --> 00:44:23,680
I won't let anyone get hurt

474
00:44:23,760 --> 00:44:26,360
because of me again. Uncle, don't worry.

475
00:44:27,000 --> 00:44:28,840
That's my girl.

476
00:44:28,920 --> 00:44:30,720
As women,

477
00:44:30,800 --> 00:44:35,000
we have to keep our dignity
and care for each other. Okay?

478
00:44:35,080 --> 00:44:37,160
Stay single with me for life.

479
00:44:37,240 --> 00:44:39,560
So you don't take someone else's love.

480
00:44:40,240 --> 00:44:41,840
I understand.

481
00:44:50,120 --> 00:44:51,840
KDMS ORTHOPEDIC HOSPITAL

482
00:45:13,200 --> 00:45:14,520
Good night.

483
00:45:16,680 --> 00:45:17,840
Thank you.

484
00:46:04,440 --> 00:46:05,720
Are you really not going to tell Pie?

485
00:46:06,920 --> 00:46:08,760
Are you running away again?

486
00:46:09,720 --> 00:46:11,200
I'm not running away this time.

487
00:46:11,280 --> 00:46:13,040
I just want to leave her life.

488
00:46:14,480 --> 00:46:15,840
If I'm not in it,

489
00:46:17,480 --> 00:46:18,960
her life will probably be better.

490
00:46:39,040 --> 00:46:41,680
WIN

491
00:46:46,200 --> 00:46:47,160
Pun.

492
00:46:47,800 --> 00:46:49,840
You knew about Dad,
so why didn't you tell me?

493
00:46:49,920 --> 00:46:51,440
Why hide it?

494
00:46:51,520 --> 00:46:52,760
Mom.

495
00:46:52,840 --> 00:46:54,520
I didn't tell you

496
00:46:55,600 --> 00:46:57,640
because I really wanted the best for you.

497
00:46:57,720 --> 00:47:00,000
I didn't want you to worry.

498
00:47:00,080 --> 00:47:02,720
If you truly want the best for me,
you must tell me the truth.

499
00:47:02,800 --> 00:47:04,480
Not team up with Dad to hide it.

500
00:47:05,320 --> 00:47:07,560
You made Mom look foolish,

501
00:47:07,640 --> 00:47:10,240
and I hate being made a fool.

502
00:47:11,400 --> 00:47:14,680
But in my life, I've never been a fool.

503
00:47:15,480 --> 00:47:18,720
I've never been tricked
or taken advantage of.

504
00:47:19,640 --> 00:47:21,960
Even with my subordinates,
I wouldn't tolerate it.

505
00:47:22,640 --> 00:47:23,520
But my wife,

506
00:47:25,080 --> 00:47:27,480
the one I love and trust, is doing this.

507
00:47:28,160 --> 00:47:29,480
I won't let it end so easily.

508
00:47:35,240 --> 00:47:36,760
I'm sorry, Mom.

509
00:47:40,120 --> 00:47:41,520
What are you going to do?

510
00:47:43,200 --> 00:47:44,480
Will you divorce Dad?

511
00:47:46,640 --> 00:47:48,440
After what he did,

512
00:47:48,520 --> 00:47:50,360
turning me into a fool,

513
00:47:51,040 --> 00:47:52,840
do you think I'd let it go that easily?

514
00:47:53,840 --> 00:47:56,440
No way. I won't divorce.

515
00:47:56,520 --> 00:47:58,240
Why should those two get to be happy?

516
00:47:58,320 --> 00:47:59,560
I won't allow it!

517
00:48:04,480 --> 00:48:07,320
<i>How can we love without suffering?</i>

518
00:48:07,400 --> 00:48:11,000
<i>Good question. There are many answers.</i>

519
00:48:11,080 --> 00:48:13,800
<i>But the one I truly believe in</i>
<i>and value most</i>

520
00:48:13,880 --> 00:48:16,760
<i>is loving with compassion.</i>

521
00:48:21,000 --> 00:48:23,280
<i>Huh? Loving with compassion?</i>

522
00:48:23,360 --> 00:48:24,840
<i>What does that mean?</i>

523
00:48:24,920 --> 00:48:27,720
<i>It means wanting them to be happy,</i>

524
00:48:28,240 --> 00:48:31,040
<i>not loving just to make ourselves happy.</i>

525
00:48:31,120 --> 00:48:32,440
<i>Wait.</i>

526
00:48:32,520 --> 00:48:35,760
<i>But if we love and we're not happy,</i>
<i>why love at all, Pek?</i>

527
00:48:36,600 --> 00:48:38,080
<i>Just listen.</i>

528
00:48:38,160 --> 00:48:41,040
<i>If we love with compassion,</i>

529
00:48:41,120 --> 00:48:42,600
<i>when they are happy,</i>

530
00:48:42,680 --> 00:48:44,800
<i>we are happy too.</i>

531
00:48:44,880 --> 00:48:48,280
<i>See? Love this way,</i>
<i>and there's no suffering.</i>

532
00:48:51,240 --> 00:48:55,000
<i>But if they're not happy,</i>
<i>then we suffer, right?</i>

533
00:48:55,080 --> 00:48:58,320
<i>If our compassion is true,</i>
<i>we won't suffer.</i>

534
00:48:58,400 --> 00:49:00,960
<i>We'll understand their pain</i>

535
00:49:01,040 --> 00:49:03,840
<i>and help ease it with understanding.</i>

536
00:49:04,520 --> 00:49:07,760
<i>You see, it's not about doing it for gain.</i>

537
00:49:07,840 --> 00:49:10,400
<i>If it were, we'd just suffer more.</i>

538
00:49:12,720 --> 00:49:16,000
<i>Oh, this is hard, Pek.</i>

539
00:49:16,520 --> 00:49:19,000
<i>Yeah, it's hard. Really hard.</i>

540
00:49:19,080 --> 00:49:22,840
<i>If it were easy, no one</i>
<i>would call my show for love advice.</i>

541
00:49:22,920 --> 00:49:24,800
<i>Well, that's true.</i>

542
00:49:27,400 --> 00:49:30,640
<i>If we can do it, we'll be able to answer</i>

543
00:49:30,720 --> 00:49:32,760
<i>the question of how to love</i>
<i>without suffering.</i>

544
00:49:32,840 --> 00:49:35,000
<i>If not yet, that's okay.</i>

545
00:49:35,080 --> 00:49:37,360
<i>Set your goal. Mark it.</i>

546
00:49:37,440 --> 00:49:40,240
<i>Then slowly practice and grow your love.</i>

547
00:49:40,320 --> 00:49:43,200
<i>One day, you'll reach the target you set.</i>

548
00:49:49,840 --> 00:49:51,120
I SAY IT LIKE THIS

549
00:49:51,200 --> 00:49:52,280
THAT'S REASONABLE. GREAT CONTENT

550
00:49:52,360 --> 00:49:53,520
SO COOL. LOVE WITH COMPASSION

551
00:49:53,600 --> 00:49:55,480
Thank you so much, Pek.

552
00:49:55,560 --> 00:49:58,400
Your show has helped me many times.

553
00:49:58,480 --> 00:49:59,400
YEAH, THANKS FOR YOUR ADVICE

554
00:49:59,480 --> 00:50:00,440
I'M ABOUT TO CRY

555
00:50:00,520 --> 00:50:04,240
I called this time
because I want my friends,

556
00:50:04,320 --> 00:50:07,560
family, and everyone around me
to hear this,

557
00:50:08,200 --> 00:50:09,880
so they don't have to suffer in love.

558
00:50:09,960 --> 00:50:10,840
WELL SAID. GAVE ME NEW PERSPECTIVE

559
00:50:11,560 --> 00:50:13,320
I want them to be happy.

560
00:50:15,440 --> 00:50:19,080
Even though we can't find perfect love
for ourselves,

561
00:50:19,160 --> 00:50:21,720
if we understand it the way you explained,

562
00:50:22,360 --> 00:50:23,520
at least

563
00:50:24,160 --> 00:50:28,400
we might suffer less, or maybe not at all.

564
00:50:31,040 --> 00:50:32,240
Thank you.

565
00:50:39,200 --> 00:50:42,320
<i>You're very welcome.</i>
<i>Wishing you good love.</i>

566
00:50:42,400 --> 00:50:43,320
<i>Good luck!</i>

567
00:50:43,400 --> 00:50:44,240
I SAY IT LIKE THIS

568
00:50:55,120 --> 00:50:58,280
<i>I listened. Thanks a lot.</i>

569
00:51:13,480 --> 00:51:17,760
THREE MONTHS LATER

570
00:51:17,840 --> 00:51:19,880
Well done.

571
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:26,120
- You're doing great. Let's step down now.
- Okay.

572
00:51:28,520 --> 00:51:30,640
- Excuse me.
- Yes.

573
00:51:35,800 --> 00:51:38,400
- I'll take over from here. Thank you.
- Sure.

574
00:51:38,480 --> 00:51:39,880
- Thank you.
- Sure.

575
00:51:43,440 --> 00:51:45,360
- Let's have a seat.
- Okay.

576
00:51:48,400 --> 00:51:49,680
How are you feeling today?

577
00:51:50,360 --> 00:51:51,880
Much better, Pun.

578
00:51:51,960 --> 00:51:53,920
I can walk without any support now.

579
00:51:55,640 --> 00:51:57,720
I feel so much more confident.

580
00:51:57,800 --> 00:51:58,800
That's great.

581
00:52:00,040 --> 00:52:01,960
I just talked to the doctor.

582
00:52:03,240 --> 00:52:05,200
Tomorrow you can go home.

583
00:52:11,040 --> 00:52:14,240
Thank you, Pun,
for taking care of me all this time.

584
00:52:16,280 --> 00:52:17,840
It's my responsibility.

585
00:52:18,960 --> 00:52:20,920
It's my duty to look after you.

586
00:52:27,800 --> 00:52:29,120
I'm…

587
00:52:31,040 --> 00:52:32,440
I'm sorry.

588
00:52:35,040 --> 00:52:36,200
It's my fault

589
00:52:36,960 --> 00:52:40,000
for lying and hiding things
from you from the start.

590
00:52:41,840 --> 00:52:43,600
That's why we had all these problems.

591
00:52:49,160 --> 00:52:50,440
I'm at fault too…

592
00:52:52,200 --> 00:52:54,080
for not understanding you.

593
00:52:57,840 --> 00:52:59,760
Have you remembered

594
00:53:01,040 --> 00:53:03,240
anything about that night yet?

595
00:53:06,400 --> 00:53:09,280
I've tried, but I just can't.

596
00:53:12,760 --> 00:53:15,360
Not remembering is better for you.

597
00:53:17,080 --> 00:53:18,640
Don't dig into it.

598
00:53:23,960 --> 00:53:25,080
Okay.

599
00:53:44,200 --> 00:53:45,240
Pie.

600
00:53:51,000 --> 00:53:53,320
Tomorrow, when you leave the hospital,

601
00:53:57,560 --> 00:53:59,200
we're getting a divorce.

602
00:54:07,360 --> 00:54:08,480
I'm sorry…

603
00:54:12,240 --> 00:54:14,720
I didn't give you what you needed.

604
00:54:18,600 --> 00:54:20,200
I just…

605
00:54:22,480 --> 00:54:23,760
wanted to win.

606
00:54:26,760 --> 00:54:28,840
And it made you suffer.

607
00:54:30,360 --> 00:54:31,760
Both physically

608
00:54:32,840 --> 00:54:34,240
and mentally.

609
00:54:36,560 --> 00:54:37,760
I'm sorry…

610
00:54:40,000 --> 00:54:41,400
for letting my anger

611
00:54:43,640 --> 00:54:45,160
punish the love

612
00:54:46,600 --> 00:54:49,000
that didn't go the way I wanted.

613
00:55:03,280 --> 00:55:05,080
I'm sorry too…

614
00:55:08,960 --> 00:55:11,440
for letting our marriage fall apart.

615
00:55:16,200 --> 00:55:17,320
I'm sorry…

616
00:55:19,560 --> 00:55:20,840
that our love

617
00:55:23,240 --> 00:55:25,680
didn't turn out

618
00:55:29,360 --> 00:55:31,160
the way we hoped.

619
00:55:34,760 --> 00:55:36,280
I'm sorry.

620
00:55:43,960 --> 00:55:45,320
Marriage

621
00:55:49,360 --> 00:55:51,560
is something we share responsibility for.

622
00:55:54,640 --> 00:55:58,480
We've both made mistakes.

623
00:56:05,240 --> 00:56:07,560
If it truly can't work,

624
00:56:12,600 --> 00:56:14,320
we should part ways

625
00:56:17,040 --> 00:56:21,360
to keep the good memories alive.

626
00:56:36,720 --> 00:56:38,560
I'm divorcing you, Pie.

627
00:56:42,080 --> 00:56:44,480
Because I want you to be happy.

628
00:57:51,960 --> 00:57:54,240
Long time no see. You've grown up.

629
00:57:54,320 --> 00:57:56,640
Am I grown enough to keep up with you?

630
00:57:57,240 --> 00:57:58,080
<i>I'm getting married.</i>

631
00:57:58,680 --> 00:58:00,720
I brought the invitations.
Here's one for you.

632
00:58:02,160 --> 00:58:07,320
<i>Some legends say it's a bad omen,</i>
<i>symbolizing death.</i>

633
00:58:07,400 --> 00:58:10,560
<i>But others believe it means love.</i>

634
00:58:10,640 --> 00:58:14,480
<i>Those who once loved will meet again.</i>

635
00:58:15,080 --> 00:58:17,440
<i>It's for the opening of Mr. Dech's museum.</i>

636
00:58:17,520 --> 00:58:19,400
<i>I want to invite you to come.</i>

637
00:58:20,200 --> 00:58:21,280
<i>I've got a task for you.</i>

638
00:58:21,360 --> 00:58:26,040
If you complete it,
your reward is my forgiveness.

639
00:58:26,120 --> 00:58:27,440
<i>Do you dare to face me?</i>

640
00:58:53,960 --> 00:58:57,920
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
